e letter to The Times.1

I cabled you on Monday last as I did not want you to gain a false impression from the report of Nigel Nicolson's2 meeting at Bournemouth on Saturday. He was reported in The Times as saying that we were not considering publication of LOLITA. It is almost impossible to know exactly what was said in the heat of an angry political meeting and he may well have inadvertently used this phrase. This of course does not represent our policy and we are going ahead with our plans to